                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/638a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-11T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1927—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>216. The Nationalist News Agency (Chinese) publishes telegram dated Hankow May 3,
                    stating Asiatic Petroleum Company operating Changsha under German management
                    until its own representative now returning to Changsha arrives.</p>
                <p>American firms restive under trade stoppage and Department is interested in any
                    attempts of other nationalities to continue or reopen commerce where Americans
                    have evacuated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
